title._content: Värske vee varumine / Collecting fresh water

description._content: Vene laevad „Nadežda“ ja „Neva“ peatusid Nuku Hiva saare juures peamiselt selleks, et täiendada proviandi varusid. Toidu osas ei kujunud peatus eriti edukaks, rohkem õnne oli laevameeskondadel aga magevee varumisel, mille juures olid ka kohalikud väga abivalmid. - - - The Russian ships Nadezhda and Neva stopped at the island of Nuku Hiva mostly to replenish their rations. The stop wasn’t very successful in terms of stocking up on food, but the ships’ crews had more luck with collecting fresh water, getting helpful support from the locals.
